Excellent movie!!! the best in this new trilogy

It's a fun film until you think about it. There are some serious issues: the sidelining of Rose, the introduction of too many new characters, some glaring moments of pure fan service, and most of all: it's far too fast and rushed and probably needed two movies to tell this one story. I'm left with no resolution, no real questions answered, and character arcs half finished. It feels rushed and messy. That being said, Daisy Ridley's performance is outstanding.

This movie is more focused on shoving in new things instead of building on what was presented in the previous movies, and as a result we get a messily paced, emotionless laundry list of things happening. There is no thematic narrative at all, making this a horrible ending to the saga. Luke, Leia, and Han died for pretty much no good reason... the Skywalkers have been destroyed.
